        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Patch Set 2:\n> \n> It looks fine. With sys.path[-1], it is the complete src path of python package that is considered.\n> The drawback is that all inputs for test to run or cnf/vnf to onboard/instantiate will have to be copied under this python path.\n> Another solution would be to consider these inputs as variable file outside the package. It looks more flexible\n\nbut for the moment we put templates dir in the package, so if we keep on putting all the needed artifacts it will be referenced.\nI think for Guilin it is acceptable, I added your proposal for an external management of the inputs (heat files, helm chart) in the etherpad",
